commit.message:
8384407: AArch64: Replace DMB + ST + DMB with STLR for C1 volatile field stores

Replaces the
 1. DMB ISH
 2. store
 3. DMB ISH
sequence with STLR for volatile field stores.
For example, this would apply to AtomicLong::set.

The DMB(1) is intended to prevent operations preceding the store(2)
from reordering with it (release barrier). The DMB (3) is intended to
prevent reordering of the store(2) with a subsequent MO_SEQ_CST load:
 DMB ISH
 STR
 DMB ISH
 LDAR

Replacing the store(2) with STLR removes a need in both DMB barriers,
as can be demonstrated with these Herd7 examples:
1. Reordering with a prior memory access is prevented.
AArch64 MP
  {
  x=0;
  y=0;
  0:X2=x; 0:X3=y;
  1:X2=x; 1:X3=y;
  }
   P0             |  P1             ;
   MOV W0,#1      |  LDR W1, [X3]   ;
   MOV W1,#1      |  DMB ISH        ;
   STR W0,  [X2]  |  LDR W0, [X2]   ;
   STLR W1, [X3]  |  ;
  ~exists
  (1:X0=0 /\ 1:X1=1)

2. Reordering with a subsequent MO_SEQ_CST load is prevented.
AArch64 MP
  {
  x=0;
  y=0;
  z=0;
  0:X2=x; 0:X3=y; 0:X4=z;
  1:X2=x; 1:X3=y;
  }
   P0             |  P1             ;
   MOV W0,#1      |  LDR W1, [X3]   ;
   MOV W1,#1      |  DMB ISH        ;
   STLR W0, [X2]  |  LDR W0, [X2]   ;
   LDAR W0, [X4]  |  ;
   STR W1,  [X3]  |  ;
  ~exists
  (1:X0=0 /\ 1:X1=1)

For other platforms, the respective membar operations are moved to
volatile_field_store as is. The volatile_field_load is adjusted
accordingly - to add a membar when the flag is set:
 `support_IRIW_for_not_multiple_copy_atomic_cpu`.
